        "details": {
            "description": "<p>A half-dozen ghostly kobolds rise from the rubble in a howling vortex.</p>",
            "disable": "<p><span data-pf2-check=\"intimidation\" data-pf2-label=\"Disable Intimidation DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"18\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Intimidation</span> (trained) to frighten the spirits with a threatening display, or <span data-pf2-check=\"religion\" data-pf2-label=\"Disable Religion DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Religion</span> (trained) to exorcise the spirits</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 2
            },
            "reset": "<p>The haunt deactivates if there are no frightened creatures in area <strong>A7</strong> at the start of its turn. The ghostly kobolds return to the rubble pile.</p>\n<p>The haunt can't activate again for 1 hour.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(1 action) The spirits swoop together toward one creature in area <strong>A7</strong> who's @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened}, instilling feelings of betrayal and confusion. The target takes [[/r 1d10+4 #mental]] mental damage (<span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"will\" data-pf2-label=\"Stonescale Spirits DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"18\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Will</span> save).</p>"
